  "id": "01KV0QKJFH82VP089MX61D4GXY",
  "title": "LurMotorn — Android App Skeleton",
  "audience": "The developer building LurMotorn (you)",
  "summary": "The Android shell for OnlyChess — deliberately thin. NativeActivity hands control to C++ (android_main in libonlychess.so); the app's CMake pulls in the shared engine + chess core; the only Kotlin is the BLE radio shim, reached from C++ over JNI. STATUS: BUILT and verified on real hardware — the debug APK installs and runs on a Samsung Galaxy A14 (arm64), and the on-device smoke test logs '20 legal moves from the start position', proving the perft-verified C++ core cross-compiles and runs under the NDK. The Vulkan renderer + BLE are still stubs (tasks #9 and #8). The final phase documents the three fixes that took the scaffold from 'never built' to 'running on a phone'.\n\nLexicon\n\n**ABI** — Application Binary Interface; the CPU target a native lib is compiled for (arm64-v8a for phones, x86_64 for the emulator).\n\n**ADB** — Android Debug Bridge; the host↔device control channel used to install/launch/log, here over Wi-Fi ('wireless debugging') instead of USB.\n\n**AGP** — Android Gradle Plugin; the Gradle plugin (8.7.3 here) that turns the project into an Android build.\n\n**android_main** — the C++ entry point native_app_glue calls; our game loop runs on the thread it provides.\n\n**android_native_app_glue** — NDK-shipped C glue that translates NativeActivity lifecycle callbacks into the simple android_main loop.\n\n**ANativeWindow** — the native handle to the on-screen surface, handed to the renderer.\n\n**APK** — Android Package; the installable app artifact (app-debug.apk).\n\n**BLE** — Bluetooth Low Energy; the only cross-platform (Android↔iPhone) link, the project's transport.\n\n**externalNativeBuild** — the Gradle hook that runs our own CMake to produce the native .so.\n\n**GATT** — Generic Attribute Profile; BLE's client/server data model used by the radio shim.\n\n**Gradle wrapper** — the committed gradlew/gradlew.bat + gradle-wrapper.jar that pin the exact Gradle version (8.9) for a reproducible build with no system Gradle.\n\n**JNI** — Java Native Interface; the calling bridge between the JVM (Kotlin) and native C++.\n\n**logcat** — Android's runtime log stream; where the on-device smoke test prints.\n\n**minSdk** — the minimum supported Android API level (26 here — the floor for modern BLE + Vulkan).\n\n**MoltenVK** — the Vulkan-over-Metal layer; the single sanctioned third-party dependency, used only on iOS.\n\n**NativeActivity** — an Android activity whose lifecycle is driven by native C++ rather than Java/Kotlin.\n\n**NDK** — Native Development Kit; Android's toolchain that compiles C/C++ with Clang for the device (27.2 here).\n\n**perft** — performance test; a move-generation node count used to verify the chess engine (20 from the start position).\n\n**.so** — shared object; a native dynamic library (here libonlychess.so, loaded by NativeActivity).\n\n**STL** — Standard Template Library; ANDROID_STL=c++_static statically links libc++ into the app.\n\n**Vulkan** — the single cross-platform GPU API the renderer targets (native on Android, via MoltenVK on iOS).",
  "generated_at": "2026-06-13T14:54:04.785Z",
  "generated_by": "claude-opus-4-7",
