      "title": "The Android shell (skeleton)",
      "summary": "How the thin Android app hands off to the shared C++ engine: NativeActivity loads libonlychess.so, android_main runs the loop, CMake pulls in the engine, and a tiny Kotlin BLE shim talks to C++ over JNI. Renderer + BLE are stubs (tasks #9/#8); nothing is built yet.",
