          "line_start": 8,
          "line_end": 40,
          "note": "Goes up to the repo root and add_subdirectory's the whole engine (tests off), so the Android lib links the SAME chess::core and lur::* targets the desktop build tests. Adds the NDK's android_native_app_glue, builds libonlychess.so, links android/log/vulkan.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KV0QMWDS2E7BK8HK7FNJZ178",
          "title": "Kotlin: a NativeActivity that just hosts the BLE shim",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Android/app/src/main/kotlin/com/lurmotorn/onlychess/OnlyChessActivity.kt",
          "line_start": 7,
          "line_end": 18,
          "note": "The only reason this Kotlin class exists: NativeActivity drives everything from C++, but we need a loaded Kotlin object (the BLE shim) for the native transport to call into via JNI. No game logic here.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KV0QMWDS2E7BK8HK7FNJZ179",
          "title": "C++ entry: the android_main loop",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Android/app/src/main/cpp/AndroidMain.cpp",
          "line_start": 47,
          "line_end": 69,
          "note": "Our loop, on the thread native_app_glue gives us. It blocks when idle and spins when there's a frame to draw, processes app/input events, and shuts the renderer down on exit. The game loop + net pump land here (tasks #9/#10).",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
