      "diagrams": [
        {
          "id": "01KV0QMWDWZ06XYRV35YAEK5BC",
          "source": "flowchart TD\n  NA[NativeActivity - OnlyChessActivity.kt] -->|loads libonlychess.so| AM[android_main - C++]\n  AM --> ENG[Shared engine + perft-verified chess core]\n  AM --> R[Vulkan renderer - stub, task 9]\n  NA --> BLE[BleShim.kt - BLE radio, task 8]\n  BLE <-->|JNI| TR[AndroidBleTransport - ITransport in C++]\n  TR --> NET[net session - C++, task 10]",
          "caption": "The Android layering. The Kotlin side is intentionally tiny: NativeActivity (which loads the native lib) and the BLE radio shim. Everything else is the shared C++ engine, reached either directly from android_main or, for the radio, across the JNI bridge. The stubbed boxes (renderer, BLE) are where tasks #8/#9 plug in."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "01KVMWYK34WZ3H7NY9W1DY1C4R",
      "title": "Building & running on-device",
      "summary": "The three concrete fixes that took the scaffold from 'never built' to 'running on a Samsung Galaxy A14'. A real CMake bug (C language never enabled), the repo's missing Gradle wrapper, and a fallback bootstrap script — then install over wireless ADB and confirm the chess core's 20-move smoke test in logcat.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "01KVMWYK35KBQWEY7730N142ZZ",
          "title": "The build-blocking bug: enable C for the NDK glue",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Android/app/src/main/cpp/CMakeLists.txt",
          "line_start": 2,
          "line_end": 3,
          "note": "project(onlychess CXX) only enabled C++, but android_native_app_glue.c is a C file. CMake then refused it with 'can not determine linker language for target: native_app_glue', failing configure for every ABI. Declaring 'C CXX' fixes it — a genuine latent bug in the skeleton, invisible until the first real NDK build.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KVMWYK35KBQWEY7730N14300",
          "title": "Pin the Gradle wrapper (8.9)",
          "code_path": "Games/Chess/Android/gradle/wrapper/gradle-wrapper.properties",
          "line_start": 3,
          "line_end": 5,
          "note": "The repo shipped only this properties file — no gradlew/gradle-wrapper.jar — and there was no system Gradle. Generating the wrapper pins Gradle 8.9 (what AGP 8.7.3 needs) and makes the build reproducible from a clean checkout. gradlew, gradlew.bat and gradle-wrapper.jar are now committed alongside it.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        },
        {
          "id": "01KVMWYK36X5XWH81VZ84WR7P1",
          "title": "Fallback bootstrap when no Gradle exists",
          "code_path": "scripts/gradle-bootstrap.ps1",
          "line_start": 10,
          "line_end": 26,
          "note": "Idempotent recovery path: if no Gradle is on the machine, download the pinned 8.9 distribution, then use it to generate the committable wrapper before building through it. This is how a fresh machine goes from zero to a wrapper-driven build without Android Studio.",
          "note_comments": [],
          "code_comments": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
